File: The Hawks made the discovery while investigating the controversial Estina Dairy case. JOHANNESBURG - Five former and current senior Free State officials will appear in the Bloemfontein Regional Court on Tuesday. The Hawks arrested them for alleged corruption, fraud and money-laundering totalling over R224-million. The suspects are allegedly linked to a company called Rekgonne Community Projects. READ: Hawks arrest four for theft of funds at a KZN TVET College The company received millions of rand from the Free State Agriculture Department between 2012 and 2016. The Hawks made the discovery while investigating the controversial Estina Dairy case.